  - STATE_UPDATE: {'patch_application_result': 'The patch has been successfully applied and state saved with an [AGENT_FIX] marker.\n\n**Summary of the fix applied to `build.sh`:**\n\nThe root cause was that Go 1.25.7 specified in `go.mod` triggers automatic toolchain download to GOMODCACHE (`/root/go/pkg/mod/golang.org/toolchain@v0.0.1-go1.25.7.linux-amd64/`). The `go-118-fuzz-build_v2` tool creates an overlay JSON that replaces `testing/fuzz.go`, but Go rejects overlays beneath GOMODCACHE.\n\nThe fix:\n1. **Downgrades the `go` directive** in all `go.mod` files from `go 1.25.7` to `go 1.25.0` (matching the installed Go version) using `sed`\n2. **Sets `GOTOOLCHAIN=local`** to prevent Go from auto-downloading a newer toolchain\n\nThis prevents the toolchain download to GOMODCACHE, allowing the `go-118-fuzz-build_v2` overlay mechanism to work correctly with the local Go installation at `/root/.go/`.'}
